  "texts": [
    "An immediate concern in discounting large, multi-authored collaborative papers (e.g., by counting a single authored paper as 1 and a 3-authored paper as a third of a paper) is that it disincentivizes large research teams as well as interdisciplinary research, which often advance the field -for example, some have shown in an analysis of over 65 million papers, patents, etc.",
    "that larger teams \"develop\" and build on past work while smaller teams \"disrupt\" existing paradigms (53).",
    "We need both approaches for scientific progress.",
    "In addition, this counting system could disincentivize giving credit where credit is due.",
    "People such as research assistants who substantially contributed are already all too often not acknowledged."
  ],
